      "content": "To make the tests more robust, we can use a combination of `page.waitForTimeout` and `page.waitForFunction` to wait for the expected elements to appear on the page. We can also use `page.waitForSelector` with a timeout to prevent the test from timing out. Here's an updated version of the test suite:\n\n```javascript\nconst test = async () => {\n  const browser = await playwright.chromium.launch();\n  const context = await browser.newContext();\n  const page = await context.newPage();\n\n  // Login\n  await page.goto('https://your-staging-url.com/login');\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"username\"]', 'your-username');\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"password\"]', 'your-password');\n  await page.click('button[type=\"submit\"]');\n\n  // Wait for login to complete\n  await page.waitForSelector('div[data-test=\"login-successful\"]', { timeout: 10000 });\n  if (!await page.$('div[data-test=\"login-successful\"]')) {\n    await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n    if (!await page.$('div[data-test=\"login-successful\"]')) {\n      throw new Error('Login failed');\n    }\n  }",
